                                                                                                               Medicine monitor in bribe net
          MANJEET SEHGAL WARRIOR                              
	Shimla, Feb. 22: The sole quality watchdog for one of the countrys pharma hubs was caught accepting a bribe from a medicine company today, police said.        
	Shamsher Singh Thakur, drug controller of Himachal Pradesh, had Rs 4.95 lakh with him  most of it in envelopes containing Rs 10,000-20,000  when vigilance authorities arrested him at Promod Pharmaceuticals unit in Solan district. Police sources said Thakur had been on a round of bribe collection.        
	Thakur is the states sole authority in approving medicines, and assessing their quality and safety. The state has attracted thousands of crores in pharma investment, with 400 factories in Solan alone. Medicines made there are sold across the country.        
	The police said even some of the drug inspectors under Thakur have amassed crores of rupees.                                                                                                                                                                            
